radiographic_examinations.findings: Right PICC tip is in a superficial vein off of the right subclavian vein. No pneumothorax. Heterogeneous opacity in the left lower lobe with blunting of the costophrenic angle is consistent with small pleural effusion. Right lung is clear without pleural effusion. Heart size, mediastinal contour, and hila are normal. No bony abnormality.
